The speed at which a system responds to requests. Performance is often measured in terms of latency (response time) and throughput (number of operations per unit time).

Examples:
- Caching
- Optimized algorithms

## Technical Patterns

### Load Balancing
Distributing incoming network traffic across multiple servers to ensure no single server bears too much load. Load balancing improves performance and reliability.

